scene.message:
Takeda: What do you brats{nl}
want? This is no place for{nl}
kids. Hey, throw those brats{nl}
out!{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Well now, how rare.{nl}
What business brings the{nl}
Nanjo family's young heir{nl}
to our humble company?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: I didn't come because{nl}
I have business with you.{nl}
I'm merely tagging along.{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Oho... Then these I{nl}
see here must be the young{nl}
master's schoolmates?{waitkey}To accompany your friends all{nl}
the way to a dreary place{nl}
like this...{wait_fr:21} ah, beautiful{nl}
friendship indeed.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: I'll thank you to stop{nl}
calling me "young master."{waitkey}I don't recall granting you{nl}
permission to address me{nl}
that way.{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Stand down, Takeda!{nl}
...{wait_fr:32}It seems the Nanjo{nl}
family's upbringing leaves{nl}
something to be desired.{waitkey}No matter. Nanjo, in time{nl}
I'll teach you how to speak{nl}
to your betters.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Nanjo's a jerk too, but{nl}
you're a way, way worse{nl}
jerk...!{waitkey}{ret}

Kandori: Understood, I'll{nl}
come shortly.{waitkey}Now then, I'll ask you all{nl}
to see yourselves out.{waitkey}{ret}

Man: Sir, do you have an{nl}
appointment for a meeting?{waitkey}I'm afraid we must ask{nl}
those without appointments{nl}
to leave.{waitkey}{ret}

{color:2}Takeda{nl}
Kandori's right-hand man, who{nl}
handles SEBEC's illegal{nl}
operations.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

{color:2}Takahisa Kandori{nl}
The ambitious branch manager{nl}
of SEBEC. Dark rumors forever{nl}
swirl around him.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}
